            . I am a <rs id="t18290910-263-viclabel1441" type="occupation">baker</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18290910-263-victim2411 t18290910-263-viclabel1441"></join>, and live in Old-street - the prisoner was in my employ for three weeks or a month. On the 8th of September my brother sent him out with a lot of bread.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18290910-263-person2413">
                  JOHN 
                  THURGOOD
               <interp inst="t18290910-263-person2413" type="surname" value="THURGOOD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290910-263-person2413" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290910-263-person2413" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am the prosecutor's brother. On the 8th of September, I gave the prisoner sixteen loaves to take to Mr. Selwin, in <placeName id="t18290910-263-crimeloc1442">Golden-lane</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18290910-263-crimeloc1442" type="placeName" value="Golden-lane"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18290910-263-crimeloc1442" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18290910-263-off1439 t18290910-263-crimeloc1442"></join>; I went the next morning, carried the bread myself, and found but twelve booked - they keep the book, but the prisoner books the bread; I know this to be the prisoner's writing - I do not know what became of the other four: he knew the book would be seen - he was discharged the next day.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18290910-263-person2414">
                  JABEZ 
                  THURGOOD
               <interp inst="t18290910-263-person2414" type="surname" value="THURGOOD"></interp>
